        <headline>Flood Advisory issued August 24 at 3:56PM PDT until August 24 at 4:45PM PDT by NWS Las Vegas NV</headline>
        <description>* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall continues.

* WHERE...A portion of southern Nevada, including the following
county, Clark.

* WHEN...Until 445 PM PDT.

* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 356 PM PDT, Doppler radar indicated decreasing shower
activity across the Henderson and Lake Mead areas. Minor
ponding from earlier rainfall remains possible. Avoid low
water crossings and flooded roads.
- Some locations that will experience flooding include...
Henderson, North Las Vegas, Boulder City, Las Vegas Bay, Lake
Las Vegas, Sam Boyd Stadium, East Las Vegas, Green Valley,
Anthem, Las Vegas Bay Campground, Railroad Pass, Boulder
Beach, Boulder Beach Campground, Hoover Dam, Callville Bay,
Callville Bay Campground, Frenchman Mtn, Sunrise Mtn and
Black Mtn.
- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood
</description>
        <instruction>Turn around, don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood
deaths occur in vehicles.</instruction>
